3#ifndef __NVBIOS_GPIO_H__
4#define __NVBIOS_GPIO_H__
5enum dcb_gpio_func_name {
6 DCB_GPIO_PANEL_POWER = 0x01,
7 DCB_GPIO_TVDAC0 = 0x0c,
8 DCB_GPIO_TVDAC1 = 0x2d,
9 DCB_GPIO_FAN = 0x09,
10 DCB_GPIO_FAN_SENSE = 0x3d,
11 DCB_GPIO_UNUSED = 0xff,
12 DCB_GPIO_VID0 = 0x04,
13 DCB_GPIO_VID1 = 0x05,
14 DCB_GPIO_VID2 = 0x06,
15 DCB_GPIO_VID3 = 0x1a,
16 DCB_GPIO_VID4 = 0x73,
17 DCB_GPIO_VID5 = 0x74,
18 DCB_GPIO_VID6 = 0x75,
19 DCB_GPIO_VID7 = 0x76,
20 DCB_GPIO_VID_PWM = 0x81,
21};
22
23#define DCB_GPIO_LOG_DIR 0x02
24#define DCB_GPIO_LOG_DIR_OUT 0x00
25#define DCB_GPIO_LOG_DIR_IN 0x02
26#define DCB_GPIO_LOG_VAL 0x01
27#define DCB_GPIO_LOG_VAL_LO 0x00
28#define DCB_GPIO_LOG_VAL_HI 0x01
29
30struct dcb_gpio_func {
31 u8 func;
32 u8 line;
33 u8 log[2];
34
35 /* so far, "param" seems to only have an influence on PWM-related
36 * GPIOs such as FAN_CONTROL and PANEL_BACKLIGHT_LEVEL.
37 * if param equals 1, hardware PWM is available
38 * if param equals 0, the host should toggle the GPIO itself
39 */
40 u8 param;
41};
42
43u16 dcb_gpio_table(struct nvkm_bios *, u8 *ver, u8 *hdr, u8 *cnt, u8 *len);
44u16 dcb_gpio_entry(struct nvkm_bios *, int idx, int ent, u8 *ver, u8 *len);
45u16 dcb_gpio_parse(struct nvkm_bios *, int idx, int ent, u8 *ver, u8 *len,
46 struct dcb_gpio_func *);
47u16 dcb_gpio_match(struct nvkm_bios *, int idx, u8 func, u8 line,
48 u8 *ver, u8 *len, struct dcb_gpio_func *);
49#endif
